14}, {\"ngram\": \"a supply crunch\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1337}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The average nightly room rate in New York City during the first quarter was $231, a nearly 7% jump from last year, according to data firm CoStar.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999997965006, \"rank\": 2.0350639005130404e-10, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrective_Optics_Space_Telescope_Axial_Replacement\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CoStar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrective_Optics_Space_Telescope_Axial_Replacement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrective_Optics_Space_Telescope_Axial_Replacement\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The average nightly room rate\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"the first quarter\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"a nearly 7% jump\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"last year\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"data firm\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"O'Neill notes one major factor behind the soaring room rates is local authorities essentially banning short-term rentals in the city.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"O'Neill\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"one major factor\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"the soaring room rates\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"local authorities\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"short-term rentals\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The New York Times reported short-term rentals represented roughly 10% of the city's travel lodging before the crackdown.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999999996032329, \"rank\": 3.9406100326536375e-10, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"short-term rentals\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly 10%\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1737}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's travel\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1758}, {\"ngram\": \"the crackdown\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city's move to convert thousands of hotel rooms into lodging for migrants has also contributed to the soaring room rates.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city's move\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"hotel rooms\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"migrants\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"the soaring room rates\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice has removed about 2% of the city's net hotel rooms from the market compared to pre-Covid levels.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The practice\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1928}, {\"ngram\": \"about 2%\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's net hotel rooms\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1979}, {\"ngram\": \"the market\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1995}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-Covid levels\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally,Air France will open an ultra-exclusive airport lounge ahead of the Paris Olympics, reports Airlines Editor Gordon 